@kaijianding `numInserted` is a count of longs and `available()` is bytes so you'll need to adjust for that.

> I think, for a closed file, available() should be equals to the length of this file, but still numInserted is better

I suppose it would be equal in common jdk implementations (so the code worked) but nothing promised it, so the code was sketchy in that regard.

@scot0357, right now the base URL is not configurable. A PR to make it configurable would be great. 

Another way to resolve above issue would be to perform rewriting of the URLs in the proxy engine. 
We did similar rewriting when working on proxying druid UIs via Apache KNOX - https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KNOX-758

@jihoonson, one thing to keep in mind is that users will probably want an option for whether to "guarantee" rollup or not. If it's guaranteed then the index task shouldn't publish early, and it probably needs to stick with two passes. If rollup is not guaranteed then we can take some short-cuts.

I haven't studied the patch yet so I'm not sure if this is addressed or not.

Sorry for commenting without reading but I just wanted to get that comment out :)

@gianm even with non-nested groupBys etc if broker is not consuming data fast enough then it will all get accumulated in SequenceInputStream created in DirectDruidClient.
However, I think I should also "decrement" total_bytes as data is consumed from SequenceInputStream, so that if broker is consuming fast enough then the total_bytes number does not grow. total_bytes then becomes total number of bytes stored there at the time and not total_bytes consumed from data nodes. How would you feel about that instead of blocking?
problem with blocking is that if multiple "bad" queries are sent then they would end up causing OOMs.
